r isn't Verant's mechanism that they have in place for taking down servers permanently when the time comes...the world-ending monster to end all monsters. Given that DAOC and SB aren't too far in the future, the time for EQ to start shrinking and for servers to get condensed may be coming...when underpopulated servers get merged and the number of servers is reduced.<P>The end of an MMOG. The industry really hasn't had to deal with that yet. I wonder when and how it will happen. The end of a world, virtual though it may be.<P>Scary, when you think about it.<P>------------------<BR>Galavant Greenlabel<BR>http://www.geocities.com/mirthandmayhem<BR>Rathe Server<P>"Judge not by size, but rather by spirit."</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rorgg</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Current story as I understand it:<P>The first 3 warders have been killed (not THAT uncommon, my guild has done it).<P>The 4th warder was attempted and FAILED, but somehow the sleeper awoke anyway and triggered the script.<P>The guild involved was accused of exploiting something to get the sleeper to spawn.  From what little they said, they claim the GM jumped to conclusions based only on the fact the script was set off.<P>All present were *suspended*.  Conquest says they'll be commenting soon.<P>Anything else at this point is speculation AFAIK.  So here's some:<P>Given the screenshot has the sleeper as Generic_Human01, I wouldn't be surprised if this were another PoM case where VI's simply not ready for something to be killed and the GMs just don't know how to procede.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">EVERY monster in the place tells you not to wake the Sleeper.<P>So if you wake the sleeper, some people have conjectured that he is supposed to come out of his tomb and kill everyone in the game.<P>Wow, imagine that! VI might have given a few large guilds the ultimate Grief PK weapon!<P>------------------<BR><B>Alliliel Archfalcon</B><BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR><A HREF="http://www.kriegeronline.com" TARGET=_blank>Krieger</A><BR>58 Levels of Loyal Service to Tunare</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Official work on their site now.<P>Someone tell the GMs that mob summoning STILL works please...<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>I am writing this now to clear up any misconceptions on what happend last night. Here is what happend...<P>We were fighting the 4th warder (ventani) and had it down to 60% or so when kerafyrm spawned, and wiped us out. Kerafyrm then killed the 4th warder.<P>Roughly 15 minutes laster, GM Valdelmar comes in and has this to say.<P>[Tue Jun 05 00:37:10 2001] Valdelmar shouts, 'Everyone that is in this zone, has a corpse in this zone, or was involved in the invasion of this zone is receiving a warning for Exploitation.'<P>Now this is where it gets good. When asked what exactly we exploited, here was the answer:<P>[Tue Jun 05 00:44:50 2001] Valdelmar tells you, 'We witnessed your clerics below the bridge keeping the warders agro by complete heal so that the tanks could safely kill. That's exploitation'<P>Now, anyone who plays the high EQ game or has a reasonable knowledge of EQ game dynamics knows that this completly IMPOSSIBLE to exploit.<P>The mobs summon ability negates this exploit 100%. If the clerics are top on aggro list, they get summoned up from below the bridge, and killed nearly instantly. The mob was on ME (the warrior) the entire battle, besides when it decided it was mad at my clerics - which is when it killed them in no time flat. In fact, if you look at the first screenshot in yesterdays update:<BR> <A HREF="http://eqconquest.inet.net.nz/img/news/st1.JPG" TARGET=_blank>http://eqconquest.inet.ne